
A *signal* is a means for the Linux/kernel to asynchronously communicate with a → Linux/kernel/process.

Use `→Linux/shell/commands/kill -l` to list implemented signals.

{ Signals
  
  { SIGTERM #sigterm
  
    Even →Linux/daemons react to this signal.
  
  }
  { SIGHUP
  }
  { SIGINT
  }
  { SIGQUIT
  }
  { SIGPIPE
  }
  { SIGCHILD
  }
  { SIGSTOP
  }
  { SIGCONT
  }
  { SIGTSTP
  }
  { SIGTTIN
  }
  { SIGTTOU
  }
  { SIGWINCH
  }

}
